Your two lovely kids...

784
00:57:18,248 --> 00:57:20,546
<i>What will become of them?</i>

785
00:57:24,421 --> 00:57:26,787
Know what?

786
00:57:26,990 --> 00:57:28,753
I make myself sick.

787
00:57:30,026 --> 00:57:35,828
But must life go on hold?
Until one's kids have left home?

788
00:57:37,300 --> 00:57:39,461
Is that the kind
of father Klara and Frederik

789
00:57:39,569 --> 00:57:42,561
will have to grow up with?

790
00:57:42,706 --> 00:57:45,231
Hey, are you two
coming down for lunch?

791
00:57:45,342 --> 00:57:48,243
It's heart casserole today.

792
00:57:48,445 --> 00:57:51,676
Go on ahead.
I'll be right with you.

793
00:57:51,782 --> 00:57:55,240
<i>Where do they get the hearts from?
Just asking.</i>

794
00:58:27,150 --> 00:58:29,744
<i>We've run out of everything.</i>

795
00:58:30,687 --> 00:58:31,881
<i>What?</i>

796
00:58:31,988 --> 00:58:34,388
Practically everything.

797
00:58:35,826 --> 00:58:38,192
Do you remember
if we're short of toilet paper?

798
00:58:40,063 --> 00:58:42,657
<i>Wake up! Toilet paper!</i>

799
00:58:43,033 --> 00:58:44,728
Jonas!

800
00:58:45,302 --> 00:58:47,497
Please!

801
00:58:48,104 --> 00:58:52,564
Don't spoil our morning.

802
00:58:53,743 --> 00:58:55,938
Make an effort.

803
00:58:59,149 --> 00:59:01,083
Mette...

804
01:01:12,148 --> 01:01:14,582
<i>Where did you get to?</i>

805
01:01:17,187 --> 01:01:19,052
I can't do it.

806
01:01:19,689 --> 01:01:21,418
Do what?

807
01:01:21,524 --> 01:01:23,253
This.

808
01:01:23,560 --> 01:01:27,860
<i>Would you rather shop elsewhere?</i>

809
01:01:29,899 --> 01:01:31,594
I'm sorry.

810
01:01:31,701 --> 01:01:33,999
Is that alcohol I smell?

811
01:01:35,238 --> 01:01:40,505
<i>We're good together in many ways,
but it's not enough.</i>

812
01:01:40,610 --> 01:01:42,578
<i>What are you saying?</i>

813
01:01:42,679 --> 01:01:44,306
I can't take it anymore.

814
01:01:44,414 --> 01:01:47,906
One day we'll die.
One day we'll have gone from here.

815
01:01:50,387 --> 01:01:52,651
<i>What are you on about?</i>

816
01:01:52,756 --> 01:01:54,690
This.

817
01:01:56,793 --> 01:01:57,885
You can't take what?

818
01:01:59,329 --> 01:02:02,059
Everything, Mette, everything.

819
01:02:07,303 --> 01:02:08,531
Are you leaving me?

820
01:02:12,375 --> 01:02:14,605
Is this a good place for it?

821
01:02:14,711 --> 01:02:17,236
No place is good for it.

822
01:02:18,014 --> 01:02:20,744
- Are you crazy?
- Everything is no more than so-so.

823
01:02:21,117 --> 01:02:24,018
But life is more
than Saturday shopping.

824
01:02:24,120 --> 01:02:25,917
- Pull yourself together!
- I want more than that.

825
01:02:30,360 --> 01:02:31,793
Is it her?

826
01:02:36,933 --> 01:02:40,198
You are destroying our lives.

827
01:02:41,571 --> 01:02:44,540
Destroying our lives!

828
01:03:58,381 --> 01:04:03,409
And finally one day you announced
with steely determination,

829
01:04:03,520 --> 01:04:08,617
"I'll never find a husband
in this poky little country. "

830
01:04:11,561 --> 01:04:15,361
"I'll have to get out there
and look for one. "

831
01:04:15,465 --> 01:04:17,057
Because, of course, you wanted
to find a man.

832
01:04:17,167 --> 01:04:18,259
Obviously.

833
01:04:18,368 --> 01:04:20,563
You'd made up your mind.

834
01:04:20,670 --> 01:04:22,831
And what kind of man?

835
01:04:22,939 --> 01:04:30,107
Not just any man: A normal man!

836
01:04:30,213 --> 01:04:36,152
The first time we saw Sebastian
we thought, "This can't be Sebastian. "

837
01:04:36,252 --> 01:04:43,624
He wasn't a rock climber
or a drug dealer or crazy in any way.

838
01:04:43,726 --> 01:04:46,490
No, he was completely normal.

839
01:04:46,596 --> 01:04:48,393
Thank you, Sebastian.

840
01:04:48,498 --> 01:04:56,098
For being so wonderfully courteous,
kind, ordinary, and normal.

841
01:04:56,206 --> 01:04:59,175
Thanks, Sebastian.

842
01:05:01,044 --> 01:05:03,979
Cheers!

843
01:05:05,648 --> 01:05:10,415
<i>The setting might have been false,
but the feeling was real.</i>

844
01:05:10,520 --> 01:05:13,250
<i>Reality was far off.</i>

845
01:05:13,356 --> 01:05:17,053
<i>I doubted
if it would ever come back.</i>

846
01:05:17,760 --> 01:05:22,094
<i>Every day postponed the day
I would tell Julia the truth.</i>

847
01:05:22,865 --> 01:05:25,698
<i>And finally it no longer mattered,</i>

848
01:05:26,202 --> 01:05:32,630
<i>for Sebastian's face took hold
and Jonas disappeared.</i>

849
01:05:57,166 --> 01:06:00,363
You didn't cash that bank check.

850
01:06:01,604 --> 01:06:03,003
<i>What check?</i>

851
01:06:05,875 --> 01:06:07,035
You are silly.

852
01:06:35,305 --> 01:06:41,301
This must be the day God created
as the prototype for all good days.

853
01:06:42,612 --> 01:06:44,409
How about we make a baby today?

854
01:06:52,722 --> 01:06:54,849
<i>We've known each other for...</i>

855
01:06:54,957 --> 01:06:59,417
Forever.

856
01:07:00,330 --> 01:07:02,059
Only forever?

857
01:07:03,132 --> 01:07:04,565
Hey?

858
01:08:56,379 --> 01:08:59,837
You'll enjoy the cottage.

859
01:09:00,850 --> 01:09:03,944
You are in no state to go anywhere.

860
01:09:04,053 --> 01:09:05,782
<i>Whether it's a cottage or not.</i>

861
01:09:05,888 --> 01:09:08,413
I don't think you should go yet.

862
01:09:09,292 --> 01:09:11,157
<i>We'll cope.</i>

863
01:09:11,761 --> 01:09:14,195
There's a lot to cope with.

864
01:09:14,797 --> 01:09:16,264
It's nice and peaceful.

865
01:09:16,632 --> 01:09:19,499
And you can phone.

866
01:09:19,602 --> 01:09:21,126
It's only an hour away.

867
01:09:21,237 --> 01:09:24,502
Quite so. Just an hour.

868
01:09:41,057 --> 01:09:43,082
Julia...

869
01:09:45,528 --> 01:09:47,860
I love you.

870
01:09:50,132 --> 01:09:52,066
Nothing can part us.

871
01:09:52,702 --> 01:09:57,036
<i>Nothing can part us.
Not even death.</i>

872
01:10:47,790 --> 01:10:50,258
I had a weird dream last night.

873
01:10:50,359 --> 01:10:52,827
I was having a swim.
A whale came along.

874
01:10:53,396 --> 01:10:57,856
It opened its mouth to swallow me.

875
01:10:57,967 --> 01:11:00,367
But standing on its tongue
was an old man

876
01:11:00,469 --> 01:11:07,432
with a Ho Chí Minh beard,
shouting, "Look out! Look out!"

877
01:11:08,744 --> 01:11:11,679
But it wasn't Ho Chí Minh.

878
01:11:11,781 --> 01:11:16,878
Because his T-shirt
had his name on: Jonah.

879
01:11:17,320 --> 01:11:21,654
I thought, why is Jonas
in the whale called Jonah?

880
01:11:21,757 --> 01:11:24,248
I don't know any Jonases.

881
01:11:25,861 --> 01:11:27,692
And why Ho Chí Minh?

882
01:11:29,632 --> 01:11:31,122
Yes, why?

883
01:11:32,268 --> 01:11:36,136
"Jonah" backwards spells "Hanoi".

884
01:11:39,208 --> 01:11:41,540
Have you ever hit me?

885
01:11:43,045 --> 01:11:45,104
No.

886
01:11:47,383 --> 01:11:49,578
Have we ever had a fight?

887
01:11:49,685 --> 01:11:50,617
No. No.

888
01:11:53,756 --> 01:11:57,453
I'll get a rug. And some tea.

889
01:12:40,469 --> 01:12:44,098
<i>You have six new messages.</i>

890
01:12:44,206 --> 01:12:46,674
<i>The first new message:</i>

891
01:12:46,776 --> 01:12:49,244
<i>Hi, it's me.
Call me. Now.</i>

892
01:12:51,881 --> 01:12:54,679
<i>Where are you?
Call me.</i>

893
01:12:57,286 --> 01:12:59,720
<i>Jonas, goddamn it!
This is bad.</i>

894
01:12:59,822 --> 01:13:02,052
<i>I've got to talk to you.</i>

895
01:13:04,660 --> 01:13:08,790
<i>I fingerprinted that wheelchair,</i>

896
01:13:08,898 --> 01:13:13,665
<i>the one you said
the Bandaged Man was in.</i>

897
01:13:13,903 --> 01:13:15,894
<i>The prints belong
to Sebastian Christersson.</i>

898
01:13:16,005 --> 01:13:19,441
<i>Call me!</i>

899
01:13:20,810 --> 01:13:22,539
I am dead.

900
01:13:24,146 --> 01:13:29,345
Do you understand?
I am dead.

901
01:13:30,019 --> 01:13:31,509
<i>I got onto Hanoi.</i>

902
01:13:31,620 --> 01:13:37,525
<i>I traced him to an apartment hotel
in Copenhagen.</i>

903
01:13:39,762 --> 01:13:45,291
<i>I'm going to pull him in and find out
what the heck is going on.</i>

904
01:13:45,401 --> 01:13:48,336
<i>You have no new messages.</i>

905
01:14:30,746 --> 01:14:34,580
- Hi.
- Hi.

906
01:14:35,050 --> 01:14:36,574
Is Julia in?

907
01:14:37,553 --> 01:14:39,180
<i>What do you want?</i>

908
01:14:40,389 --> 01:14:42,880
I am her boyfriend.

909
01:14:42,992 --> 01:14:44,459
Sebastian.

910
01:14:47,863 --> 01:14:49,558
Is she in?

911
01:14:49,665 --> 01:14:50,632
No.

912
01:14:55,805 --> 01:14:58,774
Doesn't the sign say Castlund?

913
01:14:58,874 --> 01:15:01,138
There's no Julia here.

914
01:15:01,343 --> 01:15:03,174
Sebastian!

915
01:15:10,386 --> 01:15:12,411
Julia?

916
01:15:14,490 --> 01:15:16,515
<i>Where is she?</i>

917
01:15:16,625 --> 01:15:18,889
<i>We were down by the water.</i>

918
01:15:20,396 --> 01:15:22,159
And you are...?

919
01:15:22,998 --> 01:15:25,193
<i>When did you get here?</i>

920
01:15:27,036 --> 01:15:28,196
It's a long story.

921
01:15:28,304 --> 01:15:29,396
Sebastian?

922
01:15:36,745 --> 01:15:39,737
Did you walk all the way?

923
01:15:39,849 --> 01:15:43,148
A visitor?

924
01:15:43,686 --> 01:15:45,381
<i>Who is it?</i>

925
01:15:56,465 --> 01:15:58,365
You must be Julia.

926
01:16:00,269 --> 01:16:01,736
Hi.

927
01:16:02,404 --> 01:16:03,735
My name is...

928
01:16:07,810 --> 01:16:10,108
...Jonas.

929
01:16:11,046 --> 01:16:13,776
Jonas?

930
01:16:13,883 --> 01:16:16,875
I just had a dream about you.

931
01:16:19,955 --> 01:16:20,887
You did?

932
01:16:21,056 --> 01:16:22,387
Did you come by whale?

933
01:16:26,061 --> 01:16:29,030
No, by car.
On my way to the mainland.

934
01:16:29,131 --> 01:16:32,589
Sebastian told me you were here,
so I dropped in.

935
01:16:32,701 --> 01:16:37,832
He's talked so much about you.

936
01:16:38,007 --> 01:16:39,872
Are you in a rush?

937
01:16:40,809 --> 01:16:43,437
No, not really.

938
01:16:43,545 --> 01:16:45,035
Stay for supper, then.

939
01:16:45,147 --> 01:16:47,741
- I don't want to bother you.
- Of course you must.

940
01:16:49,818 --> 01:16:52,082
Sebastian? Right?

941
01:16:55,624 --> 01:17:00,220
How can I refuse?
I've got some treats in the car.

942
01:17:03,532 --> 01:17:04,794
How lovely!

943
01:17:06,602 --> 01:17:07,967
Is there a car?

944
01:17:08,804 --> 01:17:10,101
Yes.

945
01:17:14,543 --> 01:17:16,977
So there was a Jonas.

946
01:17:19,915 --> 01:17:21,280
Yes.

947
01:17:29,858 --> 01:17:31,621
Swallow!

948
01:17:31,727 --> 01:17:32,989
Did you feel it?

949
01:17:33,095 --> 01:17:34,494
Disgusting!

950
01:17:35,998 --> 01:17:37,761
Do you always carry them
round in your trunk?

951
01:17:37,866 --> 01:17:41,563
To be quite honest,
I actually had them in my trunk

952
01:17:41,670 --> 01:17:43,035
to seduce an old girlfriend with.

953
01:17:43,138 --> 01:17:46,835
And now we're eating her oysters
and drinking her champagne.

954
01:17:46,942 --> 01:17:49,274
Aren't we lucky?

955
01:17:49,378 --> 01:17:54,543
Oh, I bet you eat them every day.
Sebastian says your family is rich.

956
01:17:54,650 --> 01:17:59,519
Does he? Hm?

957
01:17:59,621 --> 01:18:01,020
Are you completely blind?

958
01:18:01,123 --> 01:18:03,887
I can sometimes make out shadows.

959
01:18:14,970 --> 01:18:16,562
A penny for them, Sebastian?

960
01:18:16,672 --> 01:18:18,162
<i>This is sick.
What's your game?</i>

961
01:18:18,273 --> 01:18:19,900
<i>What do you mean?</i>

962
01:18:20,776 --> 01:18:23,574
Spit it out.

963
01:18:23,679 --> 01:18:24,873
<i>What?</i>

964
01:18:27,249 --> 01:18:28,716
The truth.

965
01:18:30,085 --> 01:18:31,848
I am disappointed...

966
01:18:33,889 --> 01:18:35,584
...that you haven't told Julia
about us.

967
01:18:35,691 --> 01:18:37,522
Told me what?

968
01:18:39,028 --> 01:18:41,519
<i>We were lovers.</i>

969
01:18:42,331 --> 01:18:43,764
Come off it...

970
01:18:43,866 --> 01:18:45,026
Scout's honor.

971
01:18:45,134 --> 01:18:49,730
Sebastian and I were together
for three years.

972
01:18:49,838 --> 01:18:53,604
Oh, we weren't gay gays,
we also loved women.

973
01:18:53,709 --> 01:18:59,238
Really close friends, shall we say?

974
01:18:59,348 --> 01:19:01,111
<i>Who cuddled.</i>

975
01:19:02,351 --> 01:19:05,149
Jesus, Sebastian!

976
01:19:05,921 --> 01:19:09,049
Oh, Sebastian shagged
anything that moved.

977
01:19:09,158 --> 01:19:10,989
Isn't that so, Sebastian?

978
01:19:11,093 --> 01:19:14,358
<i>What a pig!</i>

979
01:19:14,463 --> 01:19:16,124
I don't know a thing about you.

980
01:19:16,932 --> 01:19:18,763
Exactly what do you want?

981
01:19:18,867 --> 01:19:22,928
Hey, I'm sorry, I just thought
you seemed so good together.

982
01:19:23,038 --> 01:19:25,768
I didn't think you'd have secrets.

983
01:19:25,874 --> 01:19:27,899
<i>What is it that I don't know?</i>

984
01:19:28,977 --> 01:19:30,137
I'm so sorry.

985
01:19:30,245 --> 01:19:31,473
I do apologize.

986
01:19:31,580 --> 01:19:34,048
You don't have to say sorry.

987
01:19:39,154 --> 01:19:42,419
No, I know.

988
01:19:43,525 --> 01:19:45,993
I'm to blame.

989
01:19:49,765 --> 01:19:51,130
Sorry.

990
01:19:55,637 --> 01:19:57,195
Sorry, Jonas.

991
01:19:58,006 --> 01:20:02,409
It's just so long
since we last saw each other.

992
01:20:02,511 --> 01:20:05,241
<i>With good reason, of course.</i>

993
01:20:07,049 --> 01:20:11,315
But it's great that the six years
didn't wear you down completely.

994
01:20:11,420 --> 01:20:13,115
Yes, I can tell.

995
01:20:16,058 --> 01:20:18,356
Prison would be hard on anyone.

996
01:20:18,460 --> 01:20:20,553
The violence.

997
01:20:20,662 --> 01:20:22,527
No love.

998
01:20:25,300 --> 01:20:28,531
And love from the other prisoners
is not real love, is it?

999
01:20:28,637 --> 01:20:31,162
Just rape?

1000
01:20:32,241 --> 01:20:34,573
<i>What did you go to prison for?</i>

1001
01:20:35,911 --> 01:20:37,640
Drugs.

1002
01:20:37,746 --> 01:20:39,577
Jonas was a drugs runner.

1003
01:20:39,681 --> 01:20:44,243
Bumming about South East Asia
with casual jobs

1004
01:20:44,353 --> 01:20:46,321
from Beijing to Sydney.

1005
01:20:46,955 --> 01:20:50,755
Always with someone after him.
Always with a suitcase.

1006
01:20:50,859 --> 01:20:53,157
Jonas was always on the run.

1007
01:20:53,262 --> 01:20:54,786
Dear God.

1008
01:20:54,897 --> 01:20:55,955
<i>Where did you fuck up?</i>

1009
01:20:56,598 --> 01:20:58,225
Eh?

1010
01:20:58,333 --> 01:20:59,732
<i>What went wrong?</i>

1011
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:07,536
<i>Why are you telling her this?</i>

1012
01:21:09,778 --> 01:21:12,975
Have I insulted you?

1013
01:21:13,649 --> 01:21:15,844
<i>Why are you telling her I did time?</i>

1014
01:21:17,252 --> 01:21:18,549
Sebastian, what is this?

1015
01:21:18,654 --> 01:21:24,217
I'm sorry if I spoke out of turn.

1016
01:21:27,262 --> 01:21:28,627
I could tell immediately

1017
01:21:28,730 --> 01:21:31,790
that I wasn't especially
welcome today.

1018
01:21:31,900 --> 01:21:36,030
It was only because Julia insisted.

1019
01:21:41,176 --> 01:21:42,473
I'd better go.

1020
01:21:42,578 --> 01:21:44,011
Sebastian, what is going on?

1021
01:21:44,112 --> 01:21:45,101
Just what do you want?

1022
01:21:45,214 --> 01:21:48,308
Julia, I'm going.

1023
01:21:48,417 --> 01:21:51,648
Sebastian and I have had
a few issues...

1024
01:21:51,753 --> 01:21:53,846
Sit down.

1025
01:21:53,956 --> 01:21:55,423
<i>What do you want?</i>

1026
01:21:55,524 --> 01:21:58,118
Have you heard from Frank?

1027
01:21:58,227 --> 01:21:59,125
Frank?

1028
01:21:59,228 --> 01:22:01,560
Have you heard from Frank?

1029
01:22:02,231 --> 01:22:04,597
I don't know who Frank is.

1030
01:22:04,700 --> 01:22:08,295
<i>What happened in Hanoi?</i>

1031
01:22:08,403 --> 01:22:09,802
I don't know...

1032
01:22:09,905 --> 01:22:10,894
<i>What happened in Hanoi?</i>

1033
01:22:11,006 --> 01:22:12,200
You want to know?

1034
01:22:12,307 --> 01:22:13,604
Yes, I'd very much like
to hear about it.

1035
01:22:13,709 --> 01:22:17,611
I have no idea, and I have no idea
what we are talking about.

1036
01:22:17,713 --> 01:22:19,578
Tell us what happened
in Hanoi, right!

1037
01:22:19,681 --> 01:22:20,739
Stop it!

1038
01:22:22,251 --> 01:22:24,276
Go for a walk.

1039
01:22:25,287 --> 01:22:28,120
Buy some cigarettes, anything.

1040
01:22:29,258 --> 01:22:31,522
Yes.

1041
01:22:31,627 --> 01:22:34,289
Yes, a breath of air might be
a good idea

1042
01:22:34,396 --> 01:22:37,024
when you're in such a state.

1043
01:22:37,132 --> 01:22:39,225
To cool you down.

1044
01:22:44,840 --> 01:22:47,001
Know what, if you drive,
you'd better take my car.

1045
01:22:47,109 --> 01:22:49,407
It's blocking the driveway.

1046
01:22:49,511 --> 01:22:51,877
If you can be bothered to drive
such an old wreck.

1047
01:22:58,353 --> 01:23:00,548
<i>Will you be all right?</i>

1048
01:23:00,656 --> 01:23:02,419
I'll be fine.

1049
01:23:19,975 --> 01:23:22,034
<i>Frank here.</i>

1050
01:23:22,144 --> 01:23:24,874
<i>Leave a message,
and I'll call you back.</i>

1051
01:23:24,980 --> 01:23:29,747
Frank, it's me. He's here.
It's absolutely crazy.

1052
01:23:29,851 --> 01:23:32,911
I don't know what he wants.
I am by the phone.

1053
01:23:33,021 --> 01:23:34,852
Call me.

1054
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:47,561
That was stupid of me.

1055
01:23:48,370 --> 01:23:49,769
You told the truth.

1056
01:23:49,871 --> 01:23:51,600
Me and my big mouth.

1057
01:23:51,707 --> 01:23:54,369
You know how he loses his temper.

1058
01:23:56,945 --> 01:23:59,880
But he's changed incredibly.

1059
01:24:02,250 --> 01:24:03,683
Has he?

1060
01:24:04,619 --> 01:24:10,649
Sebastian has so many emotions.

1061
01:24:11,560 --> 01:24:16,862
I think he is the most
sensitive person I have ever met.

1062
01:24:16,965 --> 01:24:20,696
But sometimes things
get too much for him.

1063
01:24:21,603 --> 01:24:24,902
His love turns to...

1064
01:24:27,109 --> 01:24:29,270
...madness.

1065
01:24:30,779 --> 01:24:34,044
Do you know anything
about his exes?

1066
01:24:36,952 --> 01:24:39,648
To be perfectly honest with you,
I don't feel comfortable with this.

1067
01:24:39,755 --> 01:24:43,987
I don't like it,
but I'd rather tell the truth.

1068
01:24:45,127 --> 01:24:49,291
Do you ever feel Sebastian
is concealing stuff?

1069
01:24:51,266 --> 01:24:53,029
Yes.

1070
01:24:55,237 --> 01:24:57,535
You don't remember a thing?

1071
01:24:57,639 --> 01:24:58,765
No.

1072
01:25:00,742 --> 01:25:03,370
He claims Asia was fantastic
when you were out there.

1073
01:25:03,478 --> 01:25:05,309
<i>Wasn't it?</i>

1074
01:25:07,382 --> 01:25:09,441
Julia...

1075
01:25:12,754 --> 01:25:14,881
...I was not on my way anywhere.

1076
01:25:15,824 --> 01:25:20,591
I rushed up here the moment I heard
you were back with Sebastian.

1077
01:25:21,029 --> 01:25:22,519
Go on.

1078
01:25:23,765 --> 01:25:26,928
He was off his head
when he called me from Hanoi.

1079
01:25:28,069 --> 01:25:32,096
I don't know whether it was the acid,
but he was desperate.

1080
01:25:32,741 --> 01:25:38,338
Julia, Sebastian was the one carrying
a suitcase round Southeast Asia.

1081
01:25:38,447 --> 01:25:42,611
He worked for some
really vicious people.

1082
01:25:42,717 --> 01:25:45,880
He was smuggling diamonds,
but it went wrong.

1083
01:25:46,555 --> 01:25:50,150
And you only cheat the triads once.

1084
01:25:54,362 --> 01:25:55,852
<i>This is Frank's
answering machine.</i>

1085
01:25:55,964 --> 01:25:57,295
<i>Why didn't we escape?</i>

1086
01:25:57,399 --> 01:25:58,593
He was doomed.

1087
01:26:00,368 --> 01:26:02,666
His only way out was as a corpse.

1088
01:26:02,771 --> 01:26:04,534
<i>What happened?</i>

1089
01:26:08,310 --> 01:26:10,938
You were going to die together.

1090
01:26:21,456 --> 01:26:23,856
You've got to get us out of here.

1091
01:26:25,694 --> 01:26:26,820
Do you mean that?

1092
01:26:31,600 --> 01:26:35,798
I am with the man I got away from!

1093
01:26:36,204 --> 01:26:37,831
Yes.

1094
01:26:37,939 --> 01:26:40,430
You've got to help me.

1095
01:26:45,747 --> 01:26:48,045
<i>Calling Frank</i>

1096
01:27:03,398 --> 01:27:05,958
<i>This is Frank...</i>

1097
01:27:27,956 --> 01:27:33,155
<i>This is Frank's answering machine.
Leave a message.</i>

1098
01:27:38,867 --> 01:27:43,167
I don't get it.
Did he tell you about Hanoi?

1099
01:27:43,271 --> 01:27:44,260
You were at a hotel.

1100
01:27:46,308 --> 01:27:48,299
You left him there.

1101
01:27:50,645 --> 01:27:54,638
I keep seeing a door.

1102
01:27:55,150 --> 01:27:58,278
I am walking towards it.

1103
01:27:59,688 --> 01:28:02,521
- I mustn't go through it!
- You've got to go back.

1104
01:28:02,624 --> 01:28:05,024
Through that door.

1105
01:28:06,428 --> 01:28:10,660
You've got to go into the room.

1106
01:28:31,920 --> 01:28:32,818
They'll kill us!

1107
01:28:32,921 --> 01:28:37,756
- Give them what they want.
- It's too late.

1108
01:28:37,859 --> 01:28:39,850
It's too late, too late.

1109
01:28:39,961 --> 01:28:42,759
Let me go!

1110
01:28:49,938 --> 01:28:52,133
At least we are together.

1111
01:29:08,256 --> 01:29:11,157
<i>No, no, no!
What are you doing?</i>

1112
01:29:11,259 --> 01:29:14,695
Don't you love me?

1113
01:29:15,630 --> 01:29:20,397
I want you to tell me you love me.

1114
01:29:22,737 --> 01:29:27,071
I want you to tell me you love me.

1115
01:29:27,175 --> 01:29:32,238
I want you to tell me you love me.

1116
01:29:34,349 --> 01:29:36,840
I love you. I love you.

1117
01:29:40,889 --> 01:29:43,881
Orpheus loves you, Eurydice.

1118
01:29:47,095 --> 01:29:49,586
<i>We'll get away from all this.</i>

1119
01:29:51,733 --> 01:29:54,497
But I mustn't turn round.

1120
01:29:59,140 --> 01:30:03,406
He just wants to see
it is her following him.

1121
01:30:04,412 --> 01:30:07,973
And so she ends up back
in the Kingdom of Death.

1122
01:30:09,951 --> 01:30:14,183
And that's why they can only
be together in death.

1123
01:30:15,423 --> 01:30:17,015
Listen!

1124
01:30:18,059 --> 01:30:24,658
Orpheus must die first.
If they're to be reunited.

1125
01:30:28,336 --> 01:30:31,328
Orpheus must die first.

1126
01:30:33,241 --> 01:30:36,039
Look at me. Look at me.
Look at me.

1127
01:30:36,711 --> 01:30:38,406
I love you, Orpheus.

1128
01:30:39,414 --> 01:30:45,375
If you enter the Kingdom of Death,
I will follow you.

1129
01:30:45,487 --> 01:30:46,385
I promise.

1130
01:30:47,288 --> 01:30:48,653
I promise.

1131
01:30:49,390 --> 01:30:50,448
I promise.

1132
01:30:51,993 --> 01:31:00,298
You know I love you.

1133
01:31:00,435 --> 01:31:05,168
You promise you'll follow?
You promise you'll follow?

1134
01:31:05,273 --> 01:31:06,672
I promise.

1135
01:31:19,621 --> 01:31:24,456
Orpheus should never
have looked back.

1136
01:31:25,660 --> 01:31:28,686
You didn't want him.

1137
01:31:28,797 --> 01:31:31,789
Can you imagine how that felt?

1138
01:31:31,900 --> 01:31:36,269
Orpheus fought like fury
to reach Eurydice,

1139
01:31:36,371 --> 01:31:39,431
and when he finally made it,
there they all were, laughing.

1140
01:31:39,841 --> 01:31:44,801
"Eurydice? No, she isn't here.
She has found someone else. "

1141
01:31:50,418 --> 01:31:51,851
Come on.

1142
01:31:52,387 --> 01:31:54,617
Let's go outside and finish this.

1143
01:32:27,055 --> 01:32:28,317
Sebastian!

1144
01:32:29,757 --> 01:32:31,281
Sebastian!

1145
01:32:32,827 --> 01:32:35,057
Sebastian!

1146
01:32:50,044 --> 01:32:52,877
<i>What are you playing at, Jonas?</i>

1147
01:34:27,542 --> 01:34:29,840
You can see?

1148
01:34:32,046 --> 01:34:34,640
<i>Who are you?</i>

1149
01:35:41,349 --> 01:35:43,579
Have you started smoking again?

1150
01:35:46,454 --> 01:35:48,319
<i>What about the children?</i>

1151
01:35:48,423 --> 01:35:50,948
I only smoke under the hood.

1152
01:35:51,059 --> 01:35:53,619
I'm very careful.

1153
01:35:57,498 --> 01:36:00,126
- May I have one?
- Yes.

1154
01:36:14,715 --> 01:36:17,741
- How's the new car?
- Perfect.

1155
01:36:21,155 --> 01:36:24,147
I told you we'd need two cars.

1156
01:36:30,431 --> 01:36:31,762
I am really sorry.

1157
01:36:35,570 --> 01:36:38,130
I don't know how it got to be
such a mess.

1158
01:36:38,339 --> 01:36:41,775
It just happened.

1159
01:36:43,444 --> 01:36:46,436
The earth vanished
beneath my feet.

1160
01:36:50,585 --> 01:36:51,950
I'm not moaning.

1161
01:36:56,324 --> 01:36:58,986
But I landed very hard.

1162
01:37:02,330 --> 01:37:05,766
You always did dream of flying.

1163
01:37:06,734 --> 01:37:07,928
Yes.

1164
01:37:08,035 --> 01:37:10,128
<i>Who doesn't?</i>

1165
01:37:18,179 --> 01:37:21,444
I miss Frank.

1166
01:37:24,485 --> 01:37:31,914
Maybe he was mad,
but you could see his madness.

1167
01:37:34,595 --> 01:37:36,028
Yes.

1168
01:37:45,072 --> 01:37:46,972
Do you want to see the children?

1169
01:38:11,199 --> 01:38:13,190
<i>Wait.</i>

1170
01:38:20,208 --> 01:38:22,836
Take this damned suitcase
with you.

1171
01:38:22,944 --> 01:38:25,105
Bad karma.

1172
01:38:37,191 --> 01:38:39,182
<i>When will you be back?</i>

1173
01:38:40,094 --> 01:38:41,994
I'll call you.

1174
01:38:45,266 --> 01:38:49,032
<i>I was on my way away,
but nevertheless on my way home.</i>

1175
01:38:50,671 --> 01:38:52,798
<i>It was a good evening.</i>

1176
01:38:52,974 --> 01:38:56,876
<i>Not a Hollywood ending,
but it would do.</i>

1177
01:38:57,845 --> 01:38:59,972
<i>Like the place we live.</i>

1178
01:39:01,649 --> 01:39:03,708
<i>Not much goes on there.</i>

1179
01:39:05,620 --> 01:39:09,283
<i>But what happens
happened yesterday,</i>

1180
01:39:09,924 --> 01:39:13,291
<i>and luckily
it will happen tomorrow too.</i>

1181
01:39:13,394 --> 01:39:14,554
Sebastian!

1182
01:39:17,064 --> 01:39:18,224
Sebastian!

1183
01:39:18,532 --> 01:39:19,590
<i>Cozy.</i>

1184
01:39:19,700 --> 01:39:21,531
<i>And nice.</i>

1185
01:40:10,818 --> 01:40:12,979
<i>Here I lie.</i>

1186
01:40:15,423 --> 01:40:18,722
<i>The rain is falling on my face.</i>

1187
01:40:20,094 --> 01:40:22,358
<i>But I don't feel a thing.</i>

1188
01:40:23,731 --> 01:40:28,031
<i>In a moment they'll bring white tape
to mark out my profile.</i>

1189
01:40:29,670 --> 01:40:36,098
<i>A good shot:
The victim in the rain.</i>

1190
01:40:38,012 --> 01:40:40,412
<i>Direct flash.</i>

1191
01:40:42,249 --> 01:40:44,149
<i>Razor sharp.</i>

1192
01:40:46,354 --> 01:40:48,652
<i>The woman.</i>

1193
01:40:49,256 --> 01:40:54,125
<i>There always has to be a woman.</i>

